```

Create a file:

```bash
echo '# Git Mastery Lab' > README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "Initial commit"
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ Challenge 1 â€” Feature Branch

### Task

Add a greeting file.

```bash
git switch -c feature-greeting
echo 'puts "Hello from Git Mastery"' > greet.rb
git add greet.rb
git commit -m "Add greeting script"
```

Merge:

```bash
git switch main
git merge feature-greeting
```

âœ… Learn: fast-forward merge

---

## ğŸ”¹ Challenge 2 â€” Bad Commit & Revert

### Task

Make a bad change:

```bash
echo 'puts "BROKEN"' >> greet.rb
git commit -am "Bad change"
```

Undo safely:

```bash
git revert HEAD
```

âœ… Learn: safe undo

---

## ğŸ”¹ Challenge 3 â€” Detached HEAD

```bash
git log --oneline
git switch <old-commit-hash>
cat greet.rb
git switch main
```

âœ… Learn: history inspection

---

## ğŸ”¹ Challenge 4 â€” Reset vs Restore

```bash
echo "Temp line" >> greet.rb
git status
git restore greet.rb
```

Then:

```bash
echo "Another temp" >> greet.rb
git add greet.rb
git reset HEAD greet.rb
```

âœ… Learn: staging control

---

## ğŸ”¹ Challenge 5 â€” Stash Work

```bash
